  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The select of the modeling or programming language is based upon a number of selection criteria which need to be&#xD;
    considered. These criteria cover the need for such aspects as:-&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    An unambiguous definition language, in terms of the syntax and the semantics.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Support for modularity,&amp;nbsp;the ability&amp;nbsp;to express abstraction and deal with structured constructs.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Support for embedded real time software and runtime error handling.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A detailed explanation of the benefits and implications of using a model based approach is given in ISO 26262, volume 6&#xD;
    annex B.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For a more detailed explanation of the criteria for this clause the user is referred to ISO 26262, volume 6 clause 5.4.8.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To determine the modeling and/or the programming language to be used for the development of the safety relate software.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
